'''Black Dog Books''' is an independent publisher and production house based in [[Fitzroy, Victoria]], [[Australia]]. They publish books in all genres but focus mainly on [[children's literature]].

==History==
Black Dog Books publish books in all genres but have a main focus on [[children's literature]].<ref name="AUSTRALIANBOOKGROUP">{{cite web | url = http://www.australianbookgroup.com.au/Publishers/BlackDogBooks/ | title = Black Dog Books | publisher = Australian Book Group | date = | accessdate = 2010-05-16 |archiveurl= |archivedate= |deadurl=no}}</ref> The company's books are distributed in Australia by [[Murdoch Books]], New Zealand by [[Scholastic Corporation]], and in South Africa by [[Rynew Educational Enterprises]].<ref name="BBB ABOUT">{{cite web | url = http://www.bdb.com.au/about/ | title = About | publisher = Black Dog Books | date = | accessdate = 2010-05-16 |archiveurl= |archivedate= |deadurl=no}}</ref> Black Dog Books is also a production house, producing books for [[Horwitz Martin]] and [[Pearson Education]].<ref name="AUSTRALIANBOOKGROUP"/> The company has published multiple award winning and short-list nominee titles.<ref name="BBB AWARDS">{{cite web | url = http://www.bdb.com.au/awards/ | title = Our Awards | publisher = Black Dog Books | date = | accessdate = 2010-05-16 |archiveurl= |archivedate= |deadurl=no}}</ref> Their first winning title was in 2002 with ''[[When Mum Was Little]]'' by [[Mini Goss]] which won the [[Crichton Award for Children's Book Illustration]].<ref name="CRICHTON AWARD">{{cite web | url = http://vic.cbca.org.au/crichton.htm | title = The Crichton Award for Children's Book Illustration | publisher = [[Children's Book Council of Australia]] | date = | accessdate = 2010-05-16 |archiveurl= |archivedate= |deadurl=no}}</ref> A notable author that they publish in [[Carole Wilkinson]] whose work under Black Dog Books has won over five awards, including the [[Children's Book of the Year Award: Younger Readers]] and the [[Aurealis Award for best young-adult novel]].<ref name="BBB AWARDS"/><ref name="CBCA WINNERS20002006">{{cite web | url = http://cbca.org.au/2009.htm | title = Winners 2000 - 2006 | publisher = [[Children's Book Council of Australia]] | date = | accessdate = 2010-05-16 |archiveurl= |archivedate= |deadurl=no}}</ref><ref name="LOCUS ONLINE AA">{{cite web | url = http://www.locusmag.com/SFAwards/Db/Aurealis2004.html#yn | title = The Locus Index to SF Awards: 2004 Aurealis Awards | publisher = [[Locus Online]] | date = | accessdate = 2010-05-16 |archiveurl= |archivedate= |deadurl=no}}</ref> Other winning authors include Sue Lawson, Mark Norman, [[Pamela Freeman]], [[Danny Katz]], Ben Beaton, Leon Davidson, and Paula Hunt.<ref name="BBB AWARDS"/>

